Proof: Consider the operator 
\begin_inset Formula $e^{ix\frac{2\pi}{2L}}$
\end_inset

.
 Note that 
\begin_inset Formula $e^{ix\frac{2\pi}{2L}}\left|x'\right\rangle =e^{ix'\frac{2\pi}{2L}}\left|x'\right\rangle =e^{ix'_{mod2L}\frac{2\pi}{2L}}\left|x'\right\rangle $
\end_inset

.
 Thus, 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{mod2L}\left|x'\right\rangle =x'_{mod2L}\left|x'\right\rangle $
\end_inset

, consequently on the most general state 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|f\right\rangle \equiv\int dx'f_{x'}\left|x'\right\rangle $
\end_inset

 then, we'd have 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{mod2L}\left|f\right\rangle =\int dx'f_{x'}x'_{mod2L}\left|x'\right\rangle $
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Labeling
\labelwidthstring 00.00.0000
Remark: One needn't necessarily consider eigenstates of 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 to define the action.
 Eigenstates of 
\begin_inset Formula $e^{ix\frac{2\pi}{2L}}$
\end_inset

 maybe considered instead; they can be expressed as (a) 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\langle p+\frac{h}{2L}|\varphi\right\rangle =\left\langle p|\varphi\right\rangle $
\end_inset

