\begin_inset Formula $\left|\bar{x}\right\rangle \propto\sum_{n\in\mathbb{Z}}\left|\bar{x}+n2L\right\rangle $
\end_inset

.
 Using the second expression, we have 
\begin_inset Formula $e^{ix\frac{2\pi}{2L}}\left|\bar{x}\right\rangle =e^{i\bar{x}\frac{2\pi}{2L}}\left|\bar{x}\right\rangle $
\end_inset

.
 Thus on a more general state, 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|c\right\rangle \equiv\int_{0}^{2L}d\bar{x}c_{\bar{x}}\left|\bar{x}\right\rangle $
\end_inset

, we have 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{mod2L}\left|c\right\rangle =\int_{0}^{2L}d\bar{x}c_{\bar{x}}\bar{x}\left|\bar{x}\right\rangle $
\end_inset

.
 
